fic_pilot.py:1244:    llc_summary = run_llc_cross_check(\nscripts/scientific_pilot.py:1254:        llc_summary,\ntests/test_final_training.py:7:from scripts.final_training import FinalConfig, checkpoint_name, checkpoint_plan, select_llc_checkpoints\ntests/test_final_training.py:27:        fixed_llc_checkpoint_tokens=(0, 128, 1000),\ntests/test_final_training.py:47:    def test_llc_selection_uses_behavior_only_bracket(self) -> None:\ntests/test_final_training.py:72:        selected = select_llc_checkpoints(config, summary)\ntests/test_final_training.py:74:        self.assertTrue(selected[\"no_final_llc_inspected\"])\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:13:5. Run a 200-step sampler smoke test and generate one trace.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:15:7. Benchmark two short sampler chains with intended observables.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:38:5. Test the best two or three sampler configurations at early, middle, and late checkpoints.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:39:6. Inspect every chain trace and revise the Fermi model.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:46:- one common sampler configuration works across three checkpoints;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:62:Freeze all data, checkpoint, and behavior outputs before inspecting the final LLC trajectory.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:64:## Phase 3: LLC campaign\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:73:6. extra chains or one nearby sampler setting around the candidate interval;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:84:- LLC trajectory with chain uncertainty;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:85:- sampler diagnostic figure;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:89:- explicit limitations on transient checkpoints and sampler sensitivity.\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:100:- perform the predeclared sampler sweep;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:119:3. reduce second-seed LLC to three checkpoints;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:120:4. keep only three LLC points per control;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:121:5. reduce main seed from seven to five LLC points;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:122:6. reduce draws modestly only after running-mean stability is demonstrated;\ndocs/03_THREE_DAY_EXECUTION_PLAN.md:123:7. never drop below two chains or omit diagnostics.\nscripts/check_environment.py:33:                \"Python stack there, before rerunning the infrastructure gate.\"\nscripts/check_environment.py:41:            \"recommended_action\": \"Install a CUDA-enabled PyTorch wheel before rerunning the infrastructure gate.\",\ndocs/05_CODEX_GCP_OPERATIONS.md:77:## Long-running jobs\ndocs/05_CODEX_GCP_OPERATIONS.md:91:Do not rely on Codex remaining connected. A detached job can continue, but Codex will not autonomously resume analysis after a disconnected session unless a separate orchestrator is explicitly running.\ndocs/05_CODEX_GCP_OPERATIONS.md:104:Appropriate autonomous tasks include code fixes, short benchmark reruns, a predeclared LR grid, and a predeclared sampler grid.\ndocs/05_CODEX_GCP_OPERATIONS.md:116:The local machine is sufficient for report writing, data filtering prototypes, unit tests, and tiny CPU smoke tests. The final campaign benefits materially from a GPU because full-parameter training is repeated and SGLD requires tens of thousands of gradient-equivalent steps. A CPU-only run may be technically possible for 3M parameters but is a poor use of a three-day sprint.\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:7:The fake abstract says lexical knowledge improves smoothly, grammar improves rapidly around 3.4 million Portuguese tokens, and normalized LLC peaks then drops in the same interval. It immediately states that the result would support only a limited marker claim, not a universal phase transition.\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:20:- LLC with multiple localized SGLD chains.\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:22:The synthetic sampler diagnostic is crucial. Without a trace showing chains settle into a common range, the LLC scalar would look like an unverified function output.\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:30:In a real report, this page is valuable even if LLC later fails. It establishes whether there is a behavioral phenomenon worth explaining.\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:34:Figure 1c shows normalized LLC rising and then dropping near the grammar change. The table reports structured Portuguese, shuffled Portuguese, and matched English side by side. The most useful fabricated detail is that shuffled Portuguese reaches high lexical accuracy but near-chance grammar and no LLC changepoint. That weakens a vocabulary-only explanation.\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:40:The fake seed-level scatter places LLC and grammar changepoints near the diagonal. This is more convincing than one smooth average curve. The Spanish extension is deliberately described as exploratory because tokenization and pretraining overlap confound cross-language timing.\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:51:- LLC causes the capability;\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:58:- stable SGLD at transient checkpoints;\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:63:A real good-enough submission can be narrower: one main seed, reduced second-seed confirmation, two controls, a valid sampler diagnostic, and a cautious aligned-changepoint result.\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:73:| `figure_1c_llc_trajectory.png` | chain-level LLC aggregation |\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:74:| `figure_s1_sampler_diagnostic.png` | raw sampler loss traces |\ndocs/09_FAKE_REPORT_WALKTHROUGH.md:81:The effect sizes were selected to be visible and scientifically plausible-looking, not predicted. “3.4 million tokens,” “11.1% LLC drop,” and “418-step delay” are narrative devices. The real project should predeclare analysis and accept whatever scale or null result occurs.\nresults/02_final_training/final_training_20260620T053855Z/phase_report.md:7:- Gate decision: `proceed_to_llc`\nresults/02_final_training/final_train